<ViewTimeline>
<summary>
The <strong><c>ViewTimeline</c></strong> interface of the {{domxref(&amp;quot;Web Animations API&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Web Animations API&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;nocode&amp;quot;)}} represents a view progress timeline (see <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_scroll-driven_animations">CSS scroll-driven animations</see> for more details).
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>Pass a <c>ViewTimeline</c> instance to the <see cref="Animation.Animation"/> constructor or the <see cref="Element.Animate"/> method to specify it as the timeline that will control the progress of the animation.</para><para></para>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Animations_API">Web Animations API</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_scroll-driven_animations">CSS scroll-driven animations</see><br/>-<see cref="AnimationTimeline"/>, <see cref="ScrollTimeline"/><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ViewTimeline"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
</ViewTimeline>
<ViewTimelineViewTimeline>
<summary>
The <strong><c>ViewTimeline()</c></strong> constructor creates a new <see cref="ViewTimeline"/> object instance.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Animations_API">Web Animations API</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_scroll-driven_animations">CSS scroll-driven animations</see><br/>-<see cref="ViewTimeline"/><br/>-<see cref="AnimationTimeline"/>, <see cref="ScrollTimeline"/><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ViewTimeline/ViewTimeline"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<returns>A new <see cref="ViewTimeline"/> object instance.</returns>
</ViewTimelineViewTimeline>
<ViewTimelineEndOffset>
<summary>
The <strong><c>endOffset</c></strong> read-only property of the <see cref="ViewTimeline"/> interface returns a <see cref="CSSNumericValue"/> representing the ending (100% progress) scroll position of the timeline as an offset from the start of the overflowing section of content in the scroller.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Animations_API">Web Animations API</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_scroll-driven_animations">CSS scroll-driven animations</see><br/>-<see cref="ViewTimeline"/><br/>-<see cref="AnimationTimeline"/>, <see cref="ScrollTimeline"/><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ViewTimeline/endOffset"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A <see cref="CSSNumericValue"/>.</value>
</ViewTimelineEndOffset>
<ViewTimelineSubject>
<summary>
The <strong><c>subject</c></strong> read-only property of the <see cref="ViewTimeline"/> interface returns a reference to the subject element whose visibility within its nearest ancestor scrollable element (scroller) is driving the progress of the timeline.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Animations_API">Web Animations API</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_scroll-driven_animations">CSS scroll-driven animations</see><br/>-<see cref="ViewTimeline"/><br/>-<see cref="AnimationTimeline"/>, <see cref="ScrollTimeline"/><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ViewTimeline/subject"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>An <see cref="Element"/>.</value>
</ViewTimelineSubject>
<ViewTimelineStartOffset>
<summary>
The <strong><c>startOffset</c></strong> read-only property of the <see cref="ViewTimeline"/> interface returns a <see cref="CSSNumericValue"/> representing the starting (0% progress) scroll position of the timeline as an offset from the start of the overflowing section of content in the scroller.
</summary>
<remarks>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Animations_API">Web Animations API</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/CSS_scroll-driven_animations">CSS scroll-driven animations</see><br/>-<see cref="ViewTimeline"/><br/>-<see cref="AnimationTimeline"/>, <see cref="ScrollTimeline"/><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/ViewTimeline/startOffset"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>A <see cref="CSSNumericValue"/>.</value>
</ViewTimelineStartOffset>
